Sr. no.	Desired skills for Linux (L3)
1	What are different types of Raid ?
Raid 1 - concatenation and stripping
Raid 0 - Mirroring
RAID 5 - Stripping with parity

2	Explain how to configure new repositories or enable/disable existing repositories.

vi /etc/yum.repos.d/epel.repo
 enabled=1 to 0 
enable=1 => TO enable
enable=0 => To disable


3	How to configure logrotate to zip and remove old log files ?
truncate -5 0 /path /logfile.log


4	How to recover system in case of Kernel Panic ?
Boot the system into single user mode and login via root login credentials
cd /boot
if initrams.img is available , it must be correpted 
Now we need to check and find the kernel version
# mkinitrd initramfs -kerlel_version.img kernel_version
Boot the machine



5	How to proceed in case of hardware failure / amber alerts on hardware / server ?
6	How to repair a corrupted filesystem ?
fsck.gfs2 /dev/testvg/testlv

ext4 filesystem:
	sudo fsck.ext4 -p /dev/sdb1




